  "prompt": "What is the best therapy for dyshidrotic eczema?",
  "response": "For dyshidrotic eczema, treatment typically involves a multi-faceted approach:\n\n1. Topical treatments:\n- Corticosteroid creams\n- Topical calcineurin inhibitors\n- Moisturizers to prevent skin dryness\n\n2. Medications:\n- Oral antihistamines to reduce itching\n- Short-term oral corticosteroids for severe cases\n- Immunosuppressants like cyclosporine\n\n3. Advanced treatments:\n- Botox injections\n- Phototherapy (UV light therapy)\n- Intralesional steroid injections\n\n4. Lifestyle and home management:\n- Reduce stress\n- Avoid triggers like nickel, cobalt\n- Keep hands and feet dry\n- Use gentle, fragrance-free skincare products\n- Wear cotton gloves\n- Manage underlying conditions like allergies\n\n5. Preventive strategies:\n- Minimize hand washing\n- Use mild soaps\n- Apply barrier creams\n- Manage excessive sweating\n\nThe best therapy depends on individual case severity and specific triggers. Consulting a dermatologist for personalized treatment is recommended.\n\nMedical professionals typically start with topical treatments and progress to more advanced options if initial treatments are ineffective.",
